Kanban board is like a digital board with task cards that move from “To Do” to “Done.”


A card represents one work item.

A card could be:
  
  a task
  
  a bug
  
  a user story
  
  a feature

Columns show the stage of the work.


WIP means Work in Progress.

  A WIP limit controls how many tasks can be worked on at one time.

A blocker is something stopping the task.


